<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-10-04T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-10-04T07:00:00-05:00" n="639" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861a.00/2: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-10-04T20:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            4, 1920—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 4—3:50
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>294. Yourin<note n="80" xml:id="d639fn80">Representatrre of the
                                    provisional government at Chita.</note> announces declaration
                                Far Eastern Republic at joint meeting Amur, Vladivostok and
                                Verkhneudinsk delegations, declares the united government recently
                                established enjoys support and disinterested help of Mother Russia,
                                declares for peoples constitutional assembly, institution of private
                                ownership, taxes modified and no concession of territory [to]
                                foreign powers. Government will call upon Russian and foreign
                                capitalists to develop country. Full report by mail.<note n="81" xml:id="d639fn81">Not printed.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>